fields.description: While investing this slow DNS performance issues, I found that our dns server (UDP handler) runs in single-thread. When recursive option is enabled, this will make the DNS server unusable for any cloud of reasonable size.

comments.body: Fix is ready in my branch. I think this is 3.4.2 blocker.

[~kedwards] git show b0be8f9aa6e26a316888935debaff58954e51675

It'd be worthwhile to have independent testers to run dns tests.

Fix looks good to me.

I would prefer removing UDPWorker and using a UDPHandler per request (so UDPListener/UDPHandler would be similar to TCPListener/TCPHandler )

The UDP thread pooling looks good, would be nice to use for TCPHandlers also.

The above points could be added as bugs for 4.0 if we want to address them.

To verify this fix we used *_dnsperf_* for now. The example query file has a list of *10000000* queries. However, for quick testing we ran the test for 60 seconds and it sends 2856 queries in that period. The results varies significantly from 3.4.1 and 3.4.2 cloud.
